message.content:
Flying Officer Broughton shuffled his feet.
"Well, actually, sir, it looked like - like a bus.
A single - decker," he elaborated. "Dogfight—"
Group Captain looked. "Broughton," he said silkily.
"Didn't they teach you at Cranwell that busses are
earth-bound creatures? Aeroplanes fly, Broughton.
Busses crawl." Very pale, Broughton was. But
determined. "It was a bus, sir."
